 <tr>
  <th colspan="2" style="text-align:center">
   Notes
  </th>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td colspan="2" style="text-align:center">
   <div style="text-align: left;">
    His father was the musician
    <a href="/wiki/Vincenzo_Galilei" title="Vincenzo Galilei">
     Vincenzo Galilei
    </a>
    . Galileo Galilei's mistress
    <a href="/wiki/Marina_Gamba" title="Marina Gamba">
     Marina Gamba
    </a>
    (1570 – 21 August 1612?) bore him two daughters, (
    <a href="/wiki/Maria_Celeste" title="Maria Celeste">
     Maria Celeste
    </a>
    (Virginia, 1600–1634) and Livia (1601–1659), both of whom became
    <a href="/wiki/Nun" title="Nun">
     nuns
    </a>
    ), and a son,
    <a href="/wiki/Vincenzo_Gamba" title="Vincenzo Gamba">
     Vincenzo
    </a>
    (1606–1649), a
    <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Lutenist" title="Lutenist">
     lutenist
    </a>
    .
   </div>
  </td>
 </tr>
